It fascinates me how interconnected everyone is. Harry Houdini held a s√©ance with Theodore Roosevelt and was friends with him. Howard Lovecraft wrote a story together w/ Houdini about him boxing on top of a pyramid and escaping from underneath it (Gene Wolfe mentions it too).

In the Lovecraft story, Houdini is tricked by two men pretending to have an argument to lure him into the pyramid. In Wolfe's "Tale of the Rose and the Nightingale" a master and student pretend not to know each other to trick a boy to come with them. I'm the first to notice this!
